Suspected Corsican separatists target mayor of Bastia 
A suspected Corsican separatist bomb badly damaged the apartment of the
mayor of Bastia, Emile Zucharelli on Sunday night but caused no
casualties, police siad.
The attack was not claimed.
In other developments, a gendarmerie post at Vescovato and a hotel near
Calvi were machine-gunned.
At Hotel Paoli in Aregno near Calvi, the gunfire shattered a bay window
and a grenade was thrown under a car but failed to go off.
The two attacks were also not claimed.
Last week was marked in Corsica by almost nightly explosive and
machine-gun attacks, culminating in a rocket attack against a
gendarmerie barracks which was claimed by separatists of the FLNC.
